&gt; Hdyras followed Tankor

Tankor paused for a moment as first his drones went out taking the
point position, then the Predacons along with Hydras and a few other
drones in the rear.

The trip was largely uneventful as they made thier way towards the
mining city. As they got closer they ground became steadilly more
broken and trecherous, obviously the victim of mining and perhaps cave
ins from underground tunnels. However Tankor and his drones led Hydras
unerringly around any such real dangers, guiding them on course back
towards the city gates.

&quot;Royalty&quot; Inferno said in low tones as he came up beside Hydras,
&quot;There is no need to allow yourself to be taken into custody. I am
sure with you here we could easily overpower these guys.&quot; Inferno&#39;s
optics glowed brightly, it seemed he was eager to to do something.

&quot;We don&#39;t have time for that now!&quot; Taratulus whispered fiercely to
Inferno, &quot;If we attack now, there&#39;s no telling what else could come
out of the gates!&quot;

Inferno glanced at Taratulus and was about to say something when two
jets streaked over head with obvious Predacon signatures and marking.
From the looks of it thay appeared to be going out for some sort of
patrol.

Towards the rear most of the other Predacons were ignoring Waspinator,
as they usually did for ther most part, even Terrorsaur, who like most
of the others whowere here seemed eager to do something, anything.
Predacons were made to be warriors, and they were being hearded like
cyber-sheep to the slaughter!

